      • sorted

        public java.util.List<T> sorted()
        All the tokens encountered so far, sorted by frequency. The list is unmodifiable and backed by the model. The list is recomputed when necessary. This means that successive calls to this method will only be computationally expensive if the model is modified in between. The list is reverse-sorted by frequency, so that the highest frequency token has the lowest index (and vice versa).
        Returns:
        A list of all tokens encountered so far.
